reviews.text: Not a bad place for dinner but it does get crowded especially when it's for 2. Portions are on the small side and the setting does emulate a traditional Dai Paai Dong. Staff are friendly enough and helpful. The food was a bit salty at times but nonetheless tasty. A nice place to grab dinner a la HK if you're around TST.

Worth trying for both local and tourists

result.name: 妹記大排檔

reviews.text: 非常道地❤️
好吃😋
尖沙咀既時候已經開始去，個時價錢唔算平，但質素唔錯，份量好足，但去左旺角之後，首先佢個電梯好多人，其次食用質素及份量明顯下降。應該盡量唔會再去，始終人太多、質素服務同時下降。
排骨炒河，河粉用水灼熟 ，不是炒河是湯河，基本也做不到，不用再去了。睇落咁多好評，真是打手太多了……！
很像台灣的海產餐廳，不過是在頂樓，東西對台灣人來說可能略鹹，不過量蠻大的，服務員態度也不錯。

result.name: Kim Mui Kee Cookfood Stall

reviews.text:
Food here is absolutely awesome and affordable.

Some must-tries include:
- Spicy poached beef
- Pork knuckles (comes with free beer)
- Roasted pigeon

Most of the portions are quite big, so bring more friends!

This restaurant is like a traditional Hong Kong restaurant where the food is good, the place is crowded and noisy. From Kimberley you go in and walk down as this is in a basement. The food is delicious and good for sharing among 4-5 people. The price is also inexpensive. They serve beer here.
Excellent food and service.

It takes time to find their location. It is a bit loud and noisy but it has a variety of food selection. I love their fried rice, pork knuckle and stir fry vegetable with mince meat. Server is pretty friendly and helpful. If you want to experience cook stalk in HK, must visit!
Good food and great pricing.
